       <h2>Materials:</h2>
       <ul>
         <li>Large sticky paper</li>
         <li>Sharpie pens</li>
         <ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
       <!--<div class="Set-up"></div>-->
      <h2>Set Up:</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Write the goal of the workshop in large writing somewhere in the room that is visible to everyone </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
     <!--<div class="Instructions"></div>-->
     <h2>Intructions:</h2>
     <ol>
       <li>Read the goal statement to the participants. </li>
       <li>If you need to reach consensus, break the participants into groups of 2-3 people.</li>
       <li>Ask each group to complete the Goal Template: Our [Product/Service] that helps [Customer] to do [Task] is currently [Current State] we need to [Future State Change] because [Catalyst Driving Change]. </li>
       <li>Ask each group to present their goal statement.</li>
       <li>Pass each person a sticky dot and ask them to vote on the goal they believe should be the focus of the workshop.</li>
       <li>Ask the team if they would like to make any further updates to the wording of the statement and check that everyone is comfortable with the goal before starting.</li>
     </ol>
   </div>
